      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( صلوات الله عليه ) صَلَاةُ الزَّوَالِ صَلَاةُ الْأَوَّابِينَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Moalla Bin Muhammad, from Al Hassan Bin Ali Al Washa, from Aban Bin Usman, from Yahya Bin Abu Al A’ala, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The midday <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span> is the <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span> of the repentant’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "10. It is a narration from him (narrator of previous Hadith) by Mu‘alla’ ibn Muhammad from al-Hassan ibn Ali al-Washsha’ from Aban ibn ‘Uthman from Yahya’ ibn abu al-‘Ala’ who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘’Amir al-Mu’minin, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, “Salah (prayer) at noontime is Salah (prayer) of repenting people.’”” "
        ]
      }
